// Function to update the preview area when the mouse hovers over a thumbnail
function upDate(previewPic) {
  // Log that the event is triggering
  console.log("upDate() event triggered.");
  
  // Log the alt text and source of the hovered image
  console.log("Preview Image ALT:", previewPic.alt);
  console.log("Preview Image SRC:", previewPic.src);
  
  // Get the div with the id "image"
  var imageDiv = document.getElementById("image");
  
  // Change the text of the div to the alt text of the image
  imageDiv.innerHTML = previewPic.alt;
  
  // Change the background image of the div to the source of the hovered image
  imageDiv.style.backgroundImage = "url('" + previewPic.src + "')";
}

// Function to reset the preview area when the mouse moves away
function undo() {
  // Get the div with the id "image"
  var imageDiv = document.getElementById("image");
  
  // Reset the background image to its original (empty) state
  imageDiv.style.backgroundImage = "url('')";
  
  // Reset the text of the div to the default message
  imageDiv.innerHTML = "Hover over an image below to display here.";
}How This Works
HTML Structure:
The <div id="image"> shows the default message.
Each thumbnail image has onmouseover="upDate(this)" and onmouseout="undo()" attributes.
This passes the current image (via this) to the upDate function when hovered, and calls undo when the mouse leaves.
The upDate Function:
Uses console.log() to verify the event is firing and to log the alt text and src of the hovered image.
Finds the element with the id "image" using document.getElementById("image").
Updates the inner HTML of the div with the image’s alt text.
Updates the background image of the div to the image’s source.
The undo Function:
Resets the background image of the "image" div back to an empty URL.
Resets the text to the original default message.
Testing and Validation:
Use your browser’s console to check that the console.log() outputs appear.
Validate your HTML using the W3C Markup Validator.
Optionally, use the WAVE tool for accessibility checks.
